Interface ListenerService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EmailListenerService, FileStoringListenerService

    public interface ListenerService
    Use Java's ServiceLoader to load EventListeners

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      <T extends Event>
      Optional<EventListener<T>>      		 findListener(Class<T> eventType)
      Load event listeners that the service wants to register.

    • Method Detail

      • findListener

        <T extends Event> Optional<EventListener<T>> findListener(Class<T> eventType)
        Load event listeners that the service wants to register. These listeners will be called during regular operations and as such must never block for a prolonged period of time. Do not expect these listeners to be called in any specific order or on any specific thread.
        Parameters:
        eventType - Type of the event listener to find.
        Returns:
        A listener, if any, to register with RoboZonky.
